IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: ONE BROOKLYN HEALTH SYSTEM, INC. (THE SYSTEM), WAS FORMED IN OCTOBER 2016, AS A CHARITABLE CORPORATION ORGANIZED UNDER THE NOT-FOR-PROFIT CORPORATION LAW OF THE STATE OF NEW YORK. AMONG ITS PURPOSES, THE SYSTEM WAS FORMED TO FOSTER AND PROMOTE WELLNESS AND GENERAL HEALTH OF THE PEOPLE OF BROOKLYN, NEW YORK BY SUPPORTING AND FACILTATING THE INTEGRATION AND COODINATION OF CARE THROUGH PROMOTING AND ADVANCING RELATIONSHIPS BETWEEN HEALTHCARE INSTITUTIONS AND HEALTHCARE PROVIDERS IN BROOKLYN AND THE COMMUNITIES THEY SERVE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: MANAGEEMENT REVIEWS TRANSACTIONS TO ESTIMATE POTENTIAL TAX LIABILITIES USING A THRESHOLD OF MORE LIKELY THAN NOT OF BEING SUSTAINED. IT IS MANAGEMENT'S ESTIMATION THAT THERE ARE NO MATERIAL LIABILITIES THAT NEED TO BE RECORDED AS OF DECEMBER 31, 2022.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FORM 990 AND APPROPRIATE SCHEDULES, AS REQUIRED, IS PREPARED BY OUTSIDE ACCOUNTANTS AND REVIEWED INTERNALLY BY MANAGEMENT AND COUNSEL, AT WHICH TIME IT IS CONSIDERED THE FINAL DRAFT. THE FINAL DRAFT OF THE FORM 990 IS MADE AVAILABLE TO THE BOARD PRIOR TO IT BEING FILED WITH THE IRS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: DISCLOSURE IN ACCORDANCE WITH THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY BY EMPLOYEES AND BOARD MEMBERS THAT SATISIFY THE CRITERIA TO BE CONSIDERED "INTERESTED PERSONS' IS SUBMITTED UPON HIRING AND ANNUALLY THEREAFTER. THE AUDIT AND COMPLIANCE COMITTEE REVIEWS THE SUBMISSIONS FOR CONFLICTS AND THE OFFICE OF THE COMPLIANCE OFFICER MANAGES THE PROCESS.
